                  <handDesc>
                     <p>The handwriting, in spite of certain peculiarities, must be classed with  that of Schubart, Griech.Palaeogr. fig. 72, from the first half of the 1st century A.D. Characteristic of the style of these manuscripts are the ornamental cross lines added at the base of the vertical strokes of the letters. In this way the basic line of the writing is accentuated, whole groups of letters being joined at the bottom by continuous ornamental bars.</p>
